      "id": "A1-BG-L02-G1",
      "candidate_type": "lesson",
      "content_form": "grammar_summary",
      "explanation_md_i18n": {
        "zh_tw": "這一節總結了韓文中最重要的三個助詞：은/는、이/가、을/를。掌握這三個，就能看懂大部分的基礎句子結構。",
        "en": "This section summarizes the three most important particles in Korean: 은/는, 이/가, and 을/를. Mastering these three will allow you to understand most basic sentence structures."
      },
      "learning_role": "explicit_rule",
      "skill_focus": [
        "reading"
      ],
      "expected_output_i18n": {
        "zh_tw": "能快速理解 은/는、이/가、을/를 的基本用法差異。",
        "en": "Quickly understand the basic usage differences between 은/는, 이/가, and 을/를."
      },
      "payload": {
        "summary_items": [
          {
            "target": "名詞 + 은/는",
            "explain_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "標記「話題」。用於介紹、對比或描述一般狀態。",
              "en": "Topic marker. Used for introduction, contrast, or general description."
            }
          },
          {
            "target": "名詞 + 이/가",
            "explain_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "標記「主語」。用於指名誰是主角，或強調主語本身。",
              "en": "Subject marker. Used to spotlight the subject or designate 'who' is performing the action."
            }
          },
          {
            "target": "名詞 + 을/를",
            "explain_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "標記「受詞」。用於動作的目標或對象。",
              "en": "Object marker. Used for the target of a verb's action."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "title_i18n": {
        "zh_tw": "G1 要點總結：核心三大助詞",
        "en": "G1 Summary: The Three Core Particles"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "A1-BG-L02-G2",
      "candidate_type": "lesson",
      "content_form": "grammar_note",
      "learning_role": "explicit_rule",
      "skill_focus": [
        "reading"
      ],
      "expected_output_i18n": {
        "zh_tw": "理解韓文助詞與情境（聚光燈、話題、受詞）的聯繫。",
        "en": "Understand the relationship between Korean particles and contexts (spotlight, topic, object)."
      },
      "payload": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "title_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "主角 (이/가) vs 話題 (은/는)",
              "en": "Subject (이/가) vs Topic (은/는)"
            },
            "explanation_md_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "想像你在看一部戲。`이/가` 就像聚光燈，正打在剛出場的主角身上。而 `은/는` 則是在介紹這部戲的背景話題。\n\n- `제가 사요`：是我要請客！(强调 **我** 是請客的那個人)\n- `커피는 비싸요`：關於咖啡嘛，它很貴。(以 **咖啡** 為話題進行描述)",
              "en": "Imagine a play. `이/가` is like a spotlight on the main character who just entered. `은/는` is more about the context or background topic.\n\n- `제가 사요`: *I* am the one paying! (Spotlight on **me**)\n- `커피는 비싸요`: As for coffee, it is expensive. (Describing **coffee** as a topic)"
            }
          },
          {
            "title_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "誰被動作了？(을/를)",
              "en": "Who is the Target? (을/를)"
            },
            "explanation_md_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "當你有一個動作（動詞）時，那個「被打中」的對象就是受詞。受詞後面要加 `을/를`。\n\n- `밥을 먹어요`：吃飯。(飯是「吃」的對象)\n- `커피를 마셔요`：喝咖啡。(咖啡是「喝」的對象)",
              "en": "When you have an action (verb), the target getting 'hit' by that action is the object. Tag it with `을/를`.\n\n- `밥을 먹어요`: Eat a meal. (Meal is the object of 'eat')\n- `커피를 마셔요`: Drink coffee. (Coffee is the object of 'drink')"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "title_i18n": {
        "zh_tw": "G2 幫你整理：韓文助詞的邏輯",
        "en": "G2 Logic: Korean Particles Explained"
      }
    },
